  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Humanitarian Response and Community-based Conflict Resolution in Balkh and Herat</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">SDO will support the target community with unconditional cash, as well as peace building trainings. This intervention, at the nexus between humanitarian response and peacebuilding is vital, as SDO&apos;s analysis highlights that communities are not only suffering due to the humanitarian situation, but also due to conflict at community level, as a result of displacement.

The project will encompass two activities: Distribution of unconditional cash for the most vulnerable households in the targeted districts of Balkh and Herat, to allow them to meet their basic needs. The second area of focus will be on holding peace building workshops for 600 household heads. The project will build the capacity of the household head on mediation, negotiation and dialogue, to serve a more permanent, and sustainable, structure for continuing peace dialogue at the community levels during and beyond the life of the project.</narrative>
  </description>
